Citation.sAbstract: The (p, rho, T) properties and apparent molar volumes V/ of LiNO3 in methanol at T = (298.15 to 398.15) K and pressures up to  p = 40 MPa are reported. An empirical correlation for the apparent molar volumes of lithium nitrate in methanol with pressure, temperature  and molality has been derived. For the solutions the experiments were carried out at molalities m = (0.15512, 0.29425,  0.53931, 0.89045, 1.80347, and 3.61398) mol.kg-1 of lithium nitrate.
Citation.sTitle: (p, rho, T) properties and apparent molar volumes V/ of LiNO3 in methanol
